    <p>{`Again, we have no prior knowledge of the current situation. What Thompson Sampling will end up doing is actually creating a distribution based on returns.`}</p>
    <p>{`These distributions are representing where we think the actual expected value might lie. Using this, we can generate our own "bandit" configuration.`}</p>
    <p><strong parentName="p">{`Steps:`}</strong></p>
    <ol>
      <li parentName="ol">
        <p parentName="li">{`At each round $n$, we consider two numbers for each ad $i$`}</p>
        <ul parentName="li">
          <li parentName="ul">
            <p parentName="li">{`$N_i^1(n)$ - the number of times the ad $i$ got rewards 1 up to round $n$ `}</p>
          </li>
          <li parentName="ul">
            <p parentName="li">{`$N_i^0(n)$ - the number of times the ad $i$ got rewards 0 up to round $n$ `}</p>
          </li>
        </ul>
